Here is a JavaScript function that counts the frequency of each character in a string:

function charFrequency(str) {
  let frequency = {};
  for (let char of str) {
    if (frequency[char]) {
      frequency[char]++;
    } else {
      frequency[char] = 1;
    }
  }
  return frequency;
}

This function creates an empty object called frequency. It then iterates through each character in the string by using a for loop. If the character is already in the frequency object, the value is increased by 1. If the character is not in the frequency object, it is added as a key with a value of 1. The function ends by returning the frequency object.ffffffffff

